SYNOPSIS
========
   mixed query_notify_fail
   mixed query_notify_fail(intÂ flag)

DESCRIPTION
===========
If <flag> is not given or 0: return the string or closure which was last set
as error message for this command (with notify_fail()).

If <flag> is given and 1: return the object which issued the last
notify_fail().

If nothing was set yet, return 0.

Introduced in LDMud 3.2.7. LDMud 3.2.8 added the <flag> parameter.

      See Also:
         add_action(E), query_verb(E), query_command(E), notify_fail(E),

   *hooks*
